      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRETTY PANAMA (5) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling well back at Bendigo, but prior to that won by 3 lengths at Bendigo (24.23) beating Ivory Quill in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 on May 16. Should bounce back. CHIEF HAMISH (1) was prominent throughout when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when 4th and beaten 5.5 lengths at this track (23.23). Better than last start and can bounce back. PAW MADDOX (8) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing sixth (23.18) in a Grade 5 at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. DID SO (7) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
